    <div data-aos="fade-up" class="font-['inter'] text-justify md:text-left text-sm md:text-base mt-2 sm:mt-3 md:mt-5">
        <p>OFW Serbisyo't Kooperatiba, a public service online platform via Facebook (FB) was created since almost seven (7) years past or on 24 October 2017 by Tirso Nieva Paglicawan, Jr., formerly, the chief of Philippine Postal Corporation (PhilPost) media and public affairs; erstwhile president of PhilPost Workers Union; Cocofed scholar and editor of student publication in high school; Department of Education (DepEd) and Civil Service Commission (CSC) scholar during college at the University of the East and a civil engineering graduate; a journalist, paralegal officer and Filipino migrant workers' welfare and rights advocate/ crusader.</p>

        <p>The link of the platform is
            <a  class="text-blue-700" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://m.facebook.com/groups/1935359103456962/?ref=share&mibextid=NSMWBT">OFW Serbisyo't Kooperatiba ni Tirso Nieva Paglicawan</a>
            where the stories of the flight, plight, adventures, struggles
            and related concerns
            of overseas Filipino workers (OFWs) from home country Philippines to destination nations are chronicled; and cries and pleas of those distressed Filipino migrant workers and families are featured to obtain the attention and action of authorities!
        </p>
    </div>

    <div data-aos="fade-up" class=" mt-2 sm:mt-3 md:mt-5">
        <details class="p-2   border rounded-md w-full text-justify md:text-left font-['inter'] text-sm md:text-base">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer hover:text-indigo-600"> Read More </summary>
            <p class="mt-3">In May of 2023, OFW Serbisyo't Kooperatiba was given the privilege and opportunity by Media House Express (MHE) founders Allan Afable Hobrero, the president/ owner and Irma Espiritu Tia, MHE chief finance officer to host a daily podcast program from 6 p.m. to 7 p.m. (Philippine standard time), Monday to Friday. The show caters and is entirely dedicated to Filipino migrant workers including their families anywhere in the world who are in dire need of help. Successful stories of OFW and family members are as well presented to serve as encouragement and inspiration to countrymen. This program also is a forum and platform by, of and for cooperatives and peoples' organizations to introduce and promote their respective associations and groups.
            </p>
            <p>The link of the cited public service program at MHE, the country's first ever internet radio and television is <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-700" href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100091641682589&mibextid=ZbWKwL">Media House Express.</a></p>
